						               													<description>This is the fourth in a series of mini campaign books.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This volume, The Siege of La Crenoilis following a similar format to its predecessors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Table Top Teasers are scenarios for wargames by another name.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The intention is to provide the players with a credible military setting and objectives, which allow for rather more than simply lining up two similar armies and having a go at each other to until one destroys the other. It provides the context for the military action and allows for battles where, with quite uneven forces, both have a chance of victory depending on the setting and objectives.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This one is about a siege, in the context of a mini campaign (using a map and fighting each scenario as it arises), but without the need for much of the campaign mechanics.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are some basic rules that cover the siege works, firing and damage. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
